@startuml 31_validation_layers_architecture
!theme plain
title RAG Strategy with Multi-Layer Validation -- Component Architecture

skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #E3F2FD
  BorderColor #1565C0
  RoundCorner 10
}

left to right direction

rectangle "Query Optimization\n(LLM)" as QueryOpt #C5CAE9 {
  [Entity Extraction]
  [Ambiguity Detection]
  [Query Rewrite]
}

rectangle "CAG Layer\n(Static Context)" as CAG #C8E6C9 {
  [supported_checks.md]
  [security_patterns.json]
  [governance_rules.json]
  [pii_catalog.json]
}

rectangle "CRAG Layer\n(Dynamic Retrieval)" as CRAG #DCEDC8 {
  [Vector Search]
  [Confidence Evaluator]
  [Query Rewriter]
  [Keyword Fallback]
}

rectangle "SQL Generation\n(LLM)" as SQLGen #E1BEE7 {
  [Pattern-Based SQL]
  [Grounded Generation]
  [Explanation]
}

rectangle "Security Layer\n(Rule-Based)" as Security #FFCDD2 {
  [SELECT-Only Check]
  [Forbidden Keywords]
  [Injection Detection]
  [Multi-Statement Block]
}

rectangle "Governance Layer\n(Policy + Catalog)" as Governance #FFF9C4 {
  [PII Detection]
  [Compliance Check]
  [Access Control]
  [Approval Routing]
}

rectangle "SQL Optimization\n(LLM + Metadata)" as SQLOpt #BBDEFB {
  [Partition Push-Down]
  [Predicate Push-Down]
  [Cost Estimation]
  [Schema Validation]
}

rectangle "Duplicate Detection\n(RAG + LLM)" as DupDetect #FFE082 {
  [Vector Similarity]
  [Semantic Match (LLM)]
  [Structural Match]
  [Functional Equivalence]
}

rectangle "SQL Validation\n(Rule + LLM)" as SQLVal #C5E1A5 {
  [Syntax Check]
  [Schema Check]
  [Logical Validation (LLM)]
  [Edge Case Check (LLM)]
}

rectangle "Approval Gateway\n(Policy Router)" as Approval #F8BBD0 {
  [Owner Auto-Approve]
  [PO/TL Review]
  [DataGov Review]
  [SLA Enforcement]
}

QueryOpt --> CAG : Get static context
QueryOpt --> CRAG : Retrieve patterns
CAG --> SQLGen : Static rules
CRAG --> SQLGen : Dynamic context
SQLGen --> Security : Validate security
Security --> Governance : Check policy
Governance --> SQLOpt : Optimize
SQLOpt --> DupDetect : Check duplicate
DupDetect --> SQLVal : Validate SQL
SQLVal --> Approval : Route approval

note bottom of QueryOpt
  <b>Stage 1: LLM</b>
  Understands user intent
end note

note bottom of CAG
  <b>Stage 2: Static</b>
  Always available
  No retrieval cost
end note

note bottom of CRAG
  <b>Stage 3: RAG</b>
  Confidence-gated
  Query rewrite on MEDIUM
end note

note bottom of SQLGen
  <b>Stage 4: LLM + Context</b>
  Grounded generation
end note

note bottom of Security
  <b>Stage 5: Rule-Based</b>
  Hard blocks
  No LLM needed
end note

note bottom of Governance
  <b>Stage 6: Catalog + Policy</b>
  PII from CAG catalog
  Approval routing
end note

note bottom of SQLOpt
  <b>Stage 7: LLM + Metadata</b>
  Uses UC schema
  Cost-aware
end note

note bottom of DupDetect
  <b>Stage 8: RAG + LLM</b>
  Semantic similarity
  LLM judges match
end note

note bottom of SQLVal
  <b>Stage 9: Rule + LLM</b>
  Syntax (rule)
  Logic (LLM)
end note

note bottom of Approval
  <b>Stage 10: Policy Router</b>
  Owner/PII/Cost routing
end note

legend right
  <b>When to use LLM vs RAG vs Rule-Based?</b>
  
  <b>LLM (reasoning/generation):</b>
  - Query understanding & optimization
  - SQL generation
  - SQL optimization
  - Logical validation
  - Semantic duplicate judgment
  
  <b>RAG (grounding/retrieval):</b>
  - SQL pattern retrieval (CRAG)
  - Duplicate detection (vector search)
  - Example retrieval
  - Similar incident lookup
  
  <b>Rule-Based (deterministic checks):</b>
  - Security checks (forbidden keywords)
  - Syntax validation
  - Schema existence checks
  - PII catalog lookup
  
  <b>Hybrid (Rule + LLM):</b>
  - SQL validation (syntax + logic)
  
  <b>Hybrid (RAG + LLM):</b>
  - Duplicate detection (retrieve + judge)
  - CRAG confidence evaluation
  
  <b>Static Context (CAG):</b>
  - Small, stable docs (<5KB)
  - Always in system prompt
  - supported_checks, security_rules, pii_catalog
  
  <b>Dynamic Context (CRAG):</b>
  - Large corpus (>1GB)
  - Retrieved on-demand
  - Confidence-gated
endlegend

@enduml
